---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const rawBaseUrl = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
const baseUrl = rawBaseUrl.endsWith('/') ? rawBaseUrl : `${rawBaseUrl}/`;
---

<Layout title="Projects - Binh Pham Portfolio">
  <h1>Projects</h1>
  <p>A compiled portfolio of my graduation research, hardware engineering, and low-level firmware projects. Click on any project to explore its full technical documentation, schematics, and C/C++ code implementations:</p>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>🎓 Graduation Thesis: Design & Implementation of a High-Precision IoT Edge Gateway</h2>
    <p>
      Developed an intelligent, low-power IoT Edge Gateway running **Embedded Linux (Yocto)** to aggregate, process, and securely stream sensor data from low-power nodes to a cloud backend via concurrent Go services.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${baseUrl}projects/graduation-thesis/`} style="font-weight: 600;">Read Full Thesis Details & Architecture →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>⚖️ High-Precision Mass Measurement System (Loadcell & HX711)</h2>
    <p>
      Designed a noise-resilient electronic weight measurement node utilizing a 24-bit HX711 ADC and loadcell sensors, featuring real-time C-based Kalman and Moving Average filters to eliminate physical vibration noise.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${baseUrl}projects/loadcell-weight-system/`} style="font-weight: 600;">Read Full Project Details & C Code →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>🎙️ PDM Microphone to PCM Audio on Nordic nRF52</h2>
    <p>
      Captured high-fidelity digital microphone data using the Nordic nRF52 PDM peripheral and converted/filtered it into ready-to-use PCM audio buffers via low-latency EasyDMA double-buffering.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${baseUrl}projects/pdm-microphone-pcm-audio/`} style="font-weight: 600;">Read Full Project Details & DMA Logic →</a>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2>💾 STM32 SDMMC + DMA Debugging</h2>
    <p>
      Diagnosed and resolved critical race conditions, interrupt preemption priorities, and D-Cache memory coherence issues on STM32 microcontroller DMA transfers to SD cards via SDMMC protocol.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${baseUrl}projects/stm32-sdmmc-dma-debugging/`} style="font-weight: 600;">Read Full Debugging Journal & NVIC Details →</a>
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>